50|$|George {{fought in}} the offices of the Irish Times on Abbey Street. He ordered his men to move the huge rolls of {{printing}} paper to barricade O'Connell Street, which aided the spread of fire that burned down the GPO. At one point he risked being shot when he went to comfort a wounded British soldier, the enemy <b>holding</b> <b>fire</b> once they saw he was on a mission of mercy.|$|R
